    <!-- Application Structure Plan:
         1. Header/Hero: Introduces the research topic and context (SoC Design).
         2. Problem Dashboard: Interactive cards presenting the 4 core research questions.
         3. System Architecture Explorer: A schematic block diagram built with HTML/CSS. 
            Users click blocks (Core, Bus, Peripherals) to see implementation details relevant to RQ1 & RQ2.
            Rationale: Visualizing the SoC helps users understand the "Where" and "How" of the research.
         4. Methodology & Verification: A process flow showing how the system will be built and tested.
         5. Performance Projections: Interactive charts showing anticipated metrics (e.g., theoretical bus utilization).
            Rationale: Addresses RQ3 regarding system performance.
         6. Strategic Analysis (SWOT): Interactive toggle for Limitations vs. Opportunities (RQ4).
    -->

    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
         - Intro: Text block.
         - Research Problems: Grid of cards with hover effects. Goal: Clarity.
         - Architecture: HTML Grid/Flexbox diagram. Goal: Conceptual understanding of AXI-Lite integration. NO SVG.
         - Performance: Chart.js Line/Bar charts. Goal: Visualize the verification metrics (latency/throughput).
         - Analysis: Toggle tabs. Goal: Compare current limitations with future potential.
    -->

    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->

